name: Dratini
flavorText: It is called the "Mirage Pokemon" because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Dratini
flavorText: It is called the "Mirage Pokemon" because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.
Attack2Text: Discard the top card of your deck.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from each of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.

name: Dragonite
flavorText: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 60 damage times the number of heads.

name: Bagon
flavorText: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.

name: Shelgon
flavorText: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant it evolves.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Salamence
flavorText: As a result of its long-held dream of flying, its cellular structure changed, and wings grew out.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may have your opponent discard cards from his or her hand until he or she has 4 cards left in his or her hand.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokemon.

name: Latias
flavorText: Its body is covered in a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If Latios is on your Bench, heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Latios
flavorText: A highly intelligent Pokemon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.
Attack1Text: If Latias is on your Bench, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Rayquaza
flavorText: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on the Defending Pokemon.

name: Axew
flavorText: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for Fraxure, reveal it, and put it into your hand, Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Axew
flavorText: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Fraxure
flavorText: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they've been fighting.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is affected by a Special Condition, each of its attacks does 40 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Fraxure
flavorText: Their tusks can shatter rocks. Territory battles between Fraxure can be intensely violent.

name: Haxorus
flavorText: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Colorless Pokemon, this attack does 60 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard the top card of your deck.

name: Druddigon
flavorText: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp claws to catch prey. The skin on its face is harder than a rock.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 80 damage times the number of heads.

name: Kyurem
flavorText: It can produce ultracold air. Its body is frozen.
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
